radiographic_examinations.findings: Skin biopsy revealed infiltrate of mononuclear cells involving the upper and deep dermis, with a periadnexal pattern, sparing the epidermis and a diagnosis of acute monoblastic leukemia involving the skin.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Initially, there was noticeable regression of skin lesions after therapy; however, the rash recurred one month after completion of consolidation therapy.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Observed a rearrangement at 11q23 involving the MLL gene.
Trilineage hematopoiesis with 13% blast cells showing monocytic differentiation.
